## Wave 5 — 5-Wizard Migration + DocumentEmailWizard Fix + LegalWorkspace Consolidation

This consolidated PR ships Wave 5 of email-communication-solution-r3 per Owner Clarification (single PR for all wizard migrations).

### Empirical narrowing (per CLAUDE.md DELTA #9)
Spec FR-25 referenced "5 LegalWorkspace forks" but empirical scan confirmed only CreateMatter is a fork. Project/Event/Todo/WorkAssignment dirs in LegalWorkspace exist but have NO SendEmailStep file. Wave 5 LegalWorkspace cleanup is 1 file delete, not 5.

### Per-wizard sections

#### EntityCreationService adapter (task 070)
- `sendEmail()` refactored to ≤30 LOC thin adapter over `sendCommunication()`

#### CreateProject + CreateEvent + CreateTodo + CreateWorkAssignment (task 071)
- Shared `CreateRecordWizard/steps/SendEmailStep.tsx` migrated to canonical `<SendEmailStep />` wrapper
- One file change migrates 4 wizards (all consume the shared file)

#### CreateMatter (task 072)
- `CreateMatterWizard/SendEmailStep.tsx` migrated to canonical `<SendEmailStep />` wrapper
- Separate file from the shared step (historical divergence)

#### WorkAssignmentWizardDialog (task 073)
- Cross-package source-path import resolved to `@spaarke/ui-components`

#### LegalWorkspace (task 074)
- `CreateMatter/SendEmailStep.tsx` fork deleted
- LegalWorkspace caller now imports canonical from `@spaarke/ui-components`

#### DocumentEmailWizard latent bug fix (task 075) — FR-17
- Line 494 latent bug fixed: now uses `attachmentDriveItemIds` sourced from `driveItemId`, not `documentId`
- Closes a known production bug (attachments silently failed)

### Build + deploy
- Shared lib build clean
- LegalWorkspace solution deployed to dev
- 5 wizard solutions deployed to dev

### Test plan
Task 077 covers smoke tests for all 5 wizards + DocumentEmailWizard regression test.
```
